<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:lang="en" xml:id="aviclose"><info><pubdate>April, 2006</pubdate></info><refnamediv><refname>aviclose</refname><refpurpose>Close a video file. (experimental)</refpurpose></refnamediv>





<refsynopsisdiv><title>Calling Sequence</title><synopsis>aviclose(n)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv>
<refsection><title>Parameters</title>
<variablelist>
   <varlistentry>
   <term>n</term>
   <listitem>
   The opened file/camera index.
   </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
</variablelist>
</refsection>
<refsection><title>Description</title>
<para>
   <literal>aviclose</literal> close an opened video file or camera.
</para>
<para>
Video support for SIVP is only available when SIVP is compiled with OpenCV which support video I/O.
</para>
</refsection>
<refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
	
    n = aviopen(SCI+'/contrib/sivp/images/video.avi');
    im = avireadframe(n); //get a frame
    imshow(im);

    avishowopened()
    aviclose(n);

]]></programlisting></refsection>


